Added a stack for cells that are live at a given point in time.

You must push a frame pointing to the live cells in the following cases:

1) Before a function call, if you have different liveness than at the entry
to you. That is if anything is changed since your caller pushed his frame.

2) Especially before any call to alloc (since the GC will run if it can't
satisfy the request.

3) You must pop all frames you push before you return.
